description: Order.  As outlined in this order, defendant's motion to exclude all testimony that exposure to welding fumes causes Parkinson's Disease is denied (Related Document  255 ); Plaintiff's motion to exclude the testimony of Dr. Lee-Haley i s denied as moot without prejudice (Related document  968 ) and Defendant's motion to exclude testimony by Mr. Ewing and Dr. Zimmerman relating to issues of medical causation or toxicology is denied; Defendant's motion to exclude testimony  of Dr. Cunitz regarding the adequacy of defendants' product warnings is granted in part and denied in part; Defendant's motion to exclude testimony of Dr. Roth and Dr. Parent regarding the absorption, distribution and fate of manganese from  welding fume particles in the human body or that chronic exposure to welding fume causes injury to the central nervous system is denied; Defendant's motion to exclude testimony of Dr. Wells regarding the methodology and reliability of epidemiol ogy studies of the effects of manganese exposure in humans is denied; Defendant's motion to exclude testimony of Dr. Levy regarding what defendants knew or should have known about the neurological effects of manganese in welding fume and that de fendants did not meet his standard of occupational health practice is denied and defendant's motion to exclude testimony of Dr. Hoffman, Dr. Lecy and Dr. Zimmerman that defendants acted in an unethical manner is granted (Related Document  972 ).  Signed by Judge Kathleen M. O'Malley on 8/8/05.(R, N)
